Generally, TPA-based sensitizers can reduce aggregation and allow the interfacial electron injection of excited dye molecules into the TiO2 conduction band. Furthermore, TPA compounds can inhibit charge carriers’ recombination of the redox couple (I3-/I-\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
